# =============================================================================
# FILE: backend/.env
# =============================================================================
# PURPOSE: This file stores ALL secret values for the backend.
#          It is NEVER committed to Git. Add ".env" to your .gitignore file.
#          Each line is: KEY=value (no spaces around the = sign)
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
#   1. python-dotenv reads this file when the app starts
#   2. Each key becomes available via os.environ.get("KEY_NAME")
#   3. config.py reads these values and exposes them to app.py
#   4. app.py uses config values — never raw strings
# =============================================================================



